### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:4000/health

---

### 2. Static File (make sure ./public/styles.css exists)
GET http://localhost:4000/static/styles.css

---

### 3. Get Users (default pagination)
GET http://localhost:4000/users

---

### 4. Get Users (custom pagination)
GET http://localhost:4000/users?page=2&limit=5

---

### 5. Get User by ID (success)
GET http://localhost:4000/users/1

---

### 6. Get User by ID (not found)
GET http://localhost:4000/users/999

---

### 7. Login (get JWT token)
# @name login
POST http://localhost:4000/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

---

### 8. Login (invalid credentials – should fail 401)
POST http://localhost:4000/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}

---

### 9. Protected Profile (no token – should fail 401)
GET http://localhost:4000/profile

---

### 10. Protected Profile (with token)
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}
GET http://localhost:4000/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

---

### 11. Update User (protected – success)
PUT http://localhost:4000/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Updated"
}

---

### 12. Update User (protected – invalid body, should fail validation)
PUT http://localhost:4000/users/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": 123
}

---

### 13. Update User (protected – invalid param, should fail validation)
PUT http://localhost:4000/users/abc
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid Param"
}
